  12:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** For now only Normal Mode is supported,
  13:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** Sample and hold mode provides reduced power consumption, but requires a bit more setup.
  14:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  **
  15:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** For now connecting the DAC through other internal peripherals is also not supported.
  16:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  **
  17:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** Since the DAC channels have dedicated pins we don't need to pass in a pin config like with
  18:../libs/libDaisy/../../libs/libDaisy/src/per/dac.h ****  ** other modules. However, it is still important to not try to use the DAC pins for anything else.
